<subSubSection id="C36909B0FFA4CF006661FA66FB60107B" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BCC5A3BFFA4CF066661FA66FB961790" blockId="2.[264,1105,1428,1486]" box="[264,1105,1462,1486]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<typeStatus id="54C8E499FFA4CF066661FA66FEFA1790" box="[264,317,1462,1485]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA4CF0666F6FA67FCC11790" authority="Bellamy" authorityName="Bellamy" box="[415,774,1462,1486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Richtersveldia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insperata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA4CF0666F6FA67FD621793" box="[415,677,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Richtersveldia insperata</emphasis>
Bellamy
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2343B52FFA4CF066478FA66FCA41790" box="[785,867,1462,1485]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(present designation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC5A3BFFA4CF066661FA3FFAC514A4" blockId="2.[264,1324,1519,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Description. Small, elongate­ovoid, navicular; surface areolate to foveolate punctate, vestiture sparse; submentum subtriangular; head, pronotum evenly, transversely rounded; scutellum very small, subcircular; elytra separate, striate, subcostate, lateroposterior margins serrate; epipleuron short, not separated from elytral disc with carina; prosternum without depression for antennae in repose; process longer than wide, subquadrate; metacoxal plate without lateroposterior emargination; tibiae slightly expanded distally, apex slightly projecting, angulate; tarsi short, 
<number id="3DBB481CFFA4CF06658BF90FFCC914A4" box="[738,782,1759,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
with ventral pulvilli, claws appendiculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC5A3BFFA4CF066651F8D7FBB8152C" blockId="2.[264,1324,1519,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Etymology. This new genus­group name is feminine and is chosen to the highlight the general area, known as the Richtersveld, of the extreme northern extent of the Northern Cape Province of 
<collectingCountry id="F3641AABFFA4CF0666B2F887FDB2152C" box="[475,629,1879,1905]" name="South Africa" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, from where this new taxon was discovered.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0C0AB3FFA5CF076661F8DBFB8C153D" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" targetBox="[344,1244,290,1783]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BCC5A3BFFA5CF076661F8DBFB8C153D" blockId="3.[264,1322,1803,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA5CF076661F8DBFE48157D" bold="true" box="[264,399,1803,1824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">FIGURE 1–6</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA5CF0766F2F8DCFD41157C" box="[411,646,1804,1825]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Richtersveldia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insperata">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA5CF0766F2F8DCFD41157C" box="[411,646,1804,1825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Richtersveldia insperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, gen. &amp; sp. nov., 1, dorsal aspect; 2, lateral aspect; 3, ventral aspect; 4, head, frontal aspect; 5, antennae, dorsal aspect; 6, aedeagus, dorsal aspect; Fig. 7, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA5CF076354F8FCFE27153D" authority="Gory &amp; Laporte, 1839" authorityName="Gory &amp; Laporte" authorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Nothomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA5CF076354F8FCFAED151C" box="[1085,1322,1836,1857]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Nothomorpha 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA5CF0763A2F8FCFAED151C" authority="Gory" authorityName="Gory" authorityYear="1839" box="[1227,1322,1836,1857]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species" species="verrucosa">verrucosa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Gory &amp; Laporte, 1839
</taxonomicName>
, dorsal aspect. Scale bars = 1.0 mm, except for Fig. 5 = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCC5A3BFFA2CF006651FECCFB60107B" blockId="4.[264,1323,284,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Comments. One species unknown in modern times is 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA2CF0064BDFECCFE821303" authority="Wiedemann, 1821" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1821" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Buprestis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudis">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA2CF0064BDFECCFB4D1368" box="[980,1162,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Buprestis rudis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE227CAFFA2CF0063FEFECCFE821303" author="Wiedemann" pageId="4" pageNumber="8" refString="Wiedemann, C. R. W. (1821) Neue exotische Kafer beschrieben von C. R. W. Wiedemann u. E. F. Germar. Magazin der Entomologie, 14, 107 - 183." type="journal article" year="1821">
Wiedemann, 
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF006661FE94FE821303" box="[264,325,324,350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1821.0">1821</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was first transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA2CF0065DAFE94FC911300" box="[691,854,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Nothomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA2CF0065DAFE94FC911300" box="[691,854,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nothomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE227CAFFA2CF0064EAFE94FB821303" author="Saunders" box="[899,1093,324,350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="8" refString="Saunders, E. (1871) Catalogus Buprestidarum Synonymicus et Systematicus. J. Janson, London, 171 pp." type="book" year="1871">
Saunders (
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF006496FE94FBFB1303" box="[1023,1084,324,350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1871.0">1871</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE227CAFFA2CF006661FEBCFDA413DB" author="Kerremans" box="[264,611,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="8" refString="Kerremans, C. (1907) Monographie des buprestides, Volume 2, livraison 19, pp. 557 - 608. Dulau &amp; Co., London; Author, Bruxelles; R. Friedlander &amp; Son, Berlin." type="journal article" year="1907">
Kerremans (
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF0066F6FEBCFE1813DB" box="[415,479,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1907.0">1907</number>
: 
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF006686FEBCFD9B13DB" box="[495,604,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="577.5" valueMax="578.0" valueMin="577.0">577–578</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. At the time 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE227CAFFA2CF006478FEBCFC6813DB" author="Holm" box="[785,943,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" refString="Holm, E. (1976) Revision of the genus Nothomorpha Thomson (Coleoptera, Buprestidae). Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 39 (1), 97 - 110." type="journal article" year="1976">
Holm (
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF006403FEBCFC6013DB" box="[874,935,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1976.0">1976</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
revised 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA2CF006374FEBCFB0713D8" box="[1053,1216,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Nothomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA2CF006374FEBCFB0713D8" box="[1053,1216,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nothomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he was unable to locate the 
<typeStatus id="54C8E499FFA2CF00656DFE44FDF013F3" box="[516,567,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA2CF00650FFE44FD0013F0" box="[614,711,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Buprestis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudis">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA2CF00650FFE44FD0013F0" box="[614,711,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">B. rudis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it remains ‘incertae sedis’. From Kerremans’ (
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF006679FE6CFE8A138B" box="[272,333,444,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1907.0">1907</number>
) short redescription, it does appear to be closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA2CF0064C5FE6CFB881388" box="[940,1103,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Nothomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA2CF0064C5FE6CFB881388" box="[940,1103,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nothomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than the new species described herein, principally by the six large pronotal foveae, and the large elytral punctures in striae typical of well­known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7321B8FFA2CF006405FDDCFBC81078" box="[876,1039,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Nothomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9078629FFA2CF006405FDDCFBC81078" box="[876,1039,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nothomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. Fig. 
<number id="3DBB481CFFA2CF0063EEFDDCFB5F107B" box="[1159,1176,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="7.0">7</number>
).
</paragraph>
